      • toCharset

        public Charset toCharset()
                  throws UnsupportedCharsetException
        Converts the Character Set to a java Charset, if it can.
        Returns:
        The Java Charset.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedCharsetException - If no support for the charset is available.
        See Also:
        Supported encodings

      • names

        public String[] names()
        Returns all the names of this code. The returned array contains the following elements, with duplicated values and null values removed:

        • The programmatic name
        • The UML identifier
        • The charset name

        Those names are typically equal except for the case (programmatic names are upper case while UML names are lower case) and special characters like '-'.

        Overrides:
        names in class CodeList<CharacterSet>
        Returns:
        All names of this code constant. This array is never null and never empty.
        Since:
        2.3

        public static CharacterSet[] values()
